radiographic_examinations.findings: Mild bibasilar atelectasis; ill-defined 4.6 x 6.7 x 5.5 cm lesion superior to the expected location of the appendix with thickened, irregular enhancing periphery and linear enhancing foci likely representing thick septation. Trace free fluid in the right lower quadrant. No significant abnormalities in liver, biliary system, spleen, pancreas, kidneys, or lymph nodes.
